The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Dhoni retained at helm of Test XI 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Dhoni retained at helm of Test XI 
  - Ponting wrests ODI captaincy from Indian skipper              A STAFF REPORTER                                Mahendra Singh Dhoni      
	Calcutta: Mahendra Singh Dhoni retained his post as captain of the ICC Test Team, but lost his place to Ricky Ponting as the ODI skipper. The names were announced at the LG ICC Awards function in Bangalore on Wednesday.         
	Dhoni, who was picked to lead both the teams in 2009, was named in the ODI Team as wicket-keeper for the third year on the trot.         
	While the Indian skipper and Sachin Tendulkar made the ICC Test Team for the second year in a row, South African Dale Steyn made the grade for the third year in the running.         
	Virender Sehwag was the third Indian chosen in the Test Team.         
	Dhoni, however, was the only player who kept his place from last years ODI team, as the other ten were new entrants.         
	The ICC had named Ponting as the ODI captain in 2008 as well. There are five Australians in the side announced on Wednesday, three of whom were part of the victorious 2009 ICC Champions Trophy team in South Africa.         
	New Zealands Daniel Vettori was part of the Black Caps squad that lost to Australia Pontings men in the final.         
	The ICC announced both the teams, as chosen by a selection panel chaired by West Indian legend Clive Lloyd.         
	Test Team of the Year         
	Virender Sehwag, Simon Katich, Sachin Tendulkar, Hashim Amla, Kumar Sangakkara, Jacques Kallis, Mahendra Singh Dhoni (captain, wicket-keeper), Graeme Swann, James Anderson, Dale Steyn, Doug Bollinger         
	ODI Team of the Year         
	Sachin Tendulkar, Shane Watson, Michael Hussey, AB de Villiers, Paul Collingwood, Ricky Ponting (captain), Mahendra Singh Dhoni (wicket-keeper), Daniel Vettori, Stuart Broad, Doug Bollinger, Ryan Harris                                                                                                                     
